  "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\n`:sync-wallet-transaction` and `:check-sync` (only on non-rpc nodes) are self-firing events that `dispatch-later` themselves and form an event-loop.\r\nWhen the user logs out these events keep firing and they add up because a new event loop starts every time user logs in until the app is killed.\r\nA guard on the event that checks if the event is fired is not a complete solution because if the user logs in fast enough, the event loop is not terminated and a new one will start.\r\nA solution that would keep track of the timeouts that need to be cancelled is not easy to implement because you need to be able to flush the timeouts that have be fired.",
